---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service - ZodForge Cloud"
  description="Terms of Service for ZodForge Cloud API. Review our service agreement, usage limits, and policies."
>
  <main class="min-h-screen py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <!-- Header -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <a href="/" class="text-primary-400 hover:underline mb-4 inline-block">‚Üê Back to Home</a>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-4">Terms of Service</h1>
        <p class="text-gray-400">Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' })}</p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none">
        <!-- Introduction -->
        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">Agreement to Terms</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            By accessing or using ZodForge Cloud ("Service"), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service ("Terms").
            If you do not agree to these Terms, do not use the Service. These Terms apply to all users, including
            free tier, pro, and enterprise subscribers.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Service Description -->
        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">1. Service Description</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            ZodForge Cloud is an AI-powered schema refinement API that:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-300 space-y-2">
            <li>Analyzes Zod schemas and suggests improvements</li>
            <li>Uses OpenAI GPT-4 Turbo and Anthropic Claude 3.5 Sonnet</li>
            <li>Provides type-safe TypeScript schema generation</li>
            <li>Integrates with the ZodForge CLI tool</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mt-4">
            We strive for 99.99% uptime but do not guarantee uninterrupted service. The Service is provided "as is"
            and may be modified, suspended, or discontinued at any time.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Account Registration -->
        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">2. Account Registration</h2>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-white">2.1 Eligibility</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            You must be at least 18 years old and legally able to enter into contracts. By creating an account,
            you represent that all information provided is accurate and current.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-white">2.2 Account Security</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">You are responsible for:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-300 space-y-2">
            <li>Maintaining the confidentiality of your API keys</li>
            <li>All activities that occur under your account</li>
            <li>Notifying us immediately of unauthorized access</li>
            <li>Not sharing your account or API keys with others</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- Subscription Plans -->
        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">3. Subscription Plans & Billing</h2>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-white">3.1 Plan Tiers</h3>
          <div class="bg-gray-800/50 border border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <ul class="space-y-4 text-gray-300">
              <li>
                <strong class="text-white">Free Tier:</strong> 100 requests/month, OpenAI only, no SLA
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-white">Pro Tier ($19/month):</strong> 5,000 requests/month, OpenAI + Claude fallback,
                priority support, 99.99% uptime SLA, 7-day free trial
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-white">Enterprise Tier ($99/month):</strong> Unlimited requests, all AI providers,
                dedicated support, custom SLA, team management, 7-day free trial
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-white">3.2 Billing</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-300 space-y-2 mb-4">
            <li>Subscriptions are billed monthly in advance via Stripe</li>
            <li>All fees are in USD and exclude applicable taxes</li>
            <li>You authorize us to charge your payment method automatically</li>
            <li>Failed payments may result in service suspension</li>
            <li>Price changes will be communicated 30 days in advance</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-white">3.3 Free Trial</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Pro and Enterprise plans include a 7-day free trial. You may cancel anytime during the trial without charge.
            After the trial, your subscription begins and payment is processed.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-white">3.4 Cancellation & Refunds</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-300 space-y-2">
            <li>Cancel anytime from your account dashboard or by emailing support</li>
            <li>Cancellations take effect at the end of the current billing period</li>
            <li>No refunds for partial months unless required by law</li>
            <li><strong class="text-white">100% money-back guarantee:</strong> Full refund within 7 days of first charge (no questions asked)</li>
            <li>Downgrading to a lower tier is prorated</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- Usage Limits -->
        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">4. Usage Limits & Fair Use</h2>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-white">4.1 Rate Limits</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-300 space-y-2 mb-4">
            <li>Free: 100 requests/month, 10 requests/hour</li>
            <li>Pro: 5,000 requests/month, 100 requests/hour</li>
            <li>Enterprise: Unlimited, custom rate limits</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Exceeding limits results in 429 (Too Many Requests) responses. Unused requests do not roll over.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-white">4.2 Fair Use Policy</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            "Unlimited" plans are subject to fair use. Excessive or abusive usage (e.g., millions of requests,
            botting, reselling) may result in rate limiting or account suspension.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Acceptable Use -->
        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">5. Acceptable Use Policy</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">You agree NOT to:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-300 space-y-2">
            <li>Use the Service for illegal activities or to violate laws</li>
            <li>Transmit malware, viruses, or harmful code</li>
            <li>Attempt to bypass rate limits or security measures</li>
            <li>Reverse engineer, decompile, or hack the Service</li>
            <li>Resell or redistribute API access without authorization</li>
            <li>Send abusive, harassing, or spam content through the API</li>
            <li>Scrape, crawl, or harvest data from the Service</li>
            <li>Overload or disrupt the Service infrastructure</li>
            <li>Impersonate others or misrepresent your affiliation</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mt-4">
            Violations may result in immediate account termination without refund.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Intellectual Property -->
        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">6. Intellectual Property</h2>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-white">6.1 Our IP</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            ZodForge, the ZodForge logo, and the Service are owned by us. You may not copy, modify, or
            distribute our intellectual property without permission.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-white">6.2 Your Content</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            You retain ownership of schemas you submit. By using the Service, you grant us a license to
            process your schemas for the sole purpose of providing the Service. We do not store your schemas
            after processing (except temporary logs for debugging, deleted within 7 days).
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-white">6.3 Generated Output</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            You own the refined schemas generated by the Service. You may use them without restriction,
            including in commercial projects.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Warranties & Liability -->
        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">7. Disclaimers & Limitations</h2>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-white">7.1 No Warranties</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            THE SERVICE IS PROVIDED "AS IS" WITHOUT WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING
            BUT NOT LIMITED TO MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, OR NON-INFRINGEMENT.
            WE DO NOT GUARANTEE ACCURACY, RELIABILITY, OR AVAILABILITY.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-white">7.2 Limitation of Liability</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, WE SHALL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL,
            SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES, OR ANY LOSS OF PROFITS, REVENUE, DATA, OR USE.
            OUR TOTAL LIABILITY SHALL NOT EXCEED THE AMOUNT YOU PAID US IN THE 12 MONTHS PRIOR TO THE CLAIM.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-white">7.3 AI-Generated Content</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            AI-generated refinements are suggestions only. We are not responsible for errors, bugs, or
            issues in generated schemas. Always review and test output before production use.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Indemnification -->
        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">8. Indemnification</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            You agree to indemnify and hold us harmless from any claims, damages, losses, or expenses
            (including legal fees) arising from your use of the Service, violation of these Terms,
            or infringement of third-party rights.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Termination -->
        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">9. Termination</h2>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-white">9.1 By You</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Cancel your account anytime by emailing <a href="mailto:support@zodforge.dev" class="text-primary-400 hover:underline">support@zodforge.dev</a>.
            Cancellation takes effect at the end of the billing period.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-white">9.2 By Us</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            We may suspend or terminate your account immediately if you:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-300 space-y-2">
            <li>Violate these Terms or our Acceptable Use Policy</li>
            <li>Fail to pay fees when due</li>
            <li>Engage in fraudulent or illegal activity</li>
            <li>Pose a security risk to the Service</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mt-4">
            We will provide notice when possible but may terminate without warning for severe violations.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Changes to Terms -->
        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">10. Changes to Terms</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            We may update these Terms periodically. Material changes will be communicated via email 30 days
            in advance. Continued use after changes constitutes acceptance. If you disagree, cancel your account.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Governing Law -->
        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">11. Governing Law & Disputes</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            These Terms are governed by the laws of [Your Jurisdiction], without regard to conflict of law principles.
            Disputes shall be resolved through binding arbitration in accordance with [Arbitration Rules].
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            You waive the right to a jury trial and class action lawsuits.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Miscellaneous -->
        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">12. Miscellaneous</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-300 space-y-2">
            <li><strong class="text-white">Entire Agreement:</strong> These Terms constitute the entire agreement between you and us.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-white">Severability:</strong> If any provision is invalid, the remainder remains in effect.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-white">Waiver:</strong> Failure to enforce any right does not waive that right.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-white">Assignment:</strong> You may not assign these Terms; we may assign without notice.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-white">Force Majeure:</strong> We are not liable for delays due to events beyond our control.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- Contact -->
        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">13. Contact Information</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Questions about these Terms? Contact us:
          </p>
          <div class="bg-gray-800/50 border border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-6">
            <p class="text-gray-300">
              <strong class="text-white">Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:legal@zodforge.dev" class="text-primary-400 hover:underline">legal@zodforge.dev</a><br />
              <strong class="text-white">Support:</strong> <a href="mailto:support@zodforge.dev" class="text-primary-400 hover:underline">support@zodforge.dev</a><br />
              <strong class="text-white">Website:</strong> <a href="https://zodforge.dev" class="text-primary-400 hover:underline">https://zodforge.dev</a>
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Acceptance -->
        <div class="bg-primary-600/10 border border-primary-600/30 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            <strong class="text-white">By using ZodForge Cloud, you acknowledge that you have read, understood,
            and agree to be bound by these Terms of Service.</strong>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .prose h2 {
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }
  .prose h3 {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }
  .prose a {
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }
</style>
